  "text": "The Java class loading delegation chain starts with ClassLoader.loadClass(String, boolean) in ClassLoader.java, which implements parent-first delegation: it first checks whether the class is already loaded, then delegates to the parent loader before attempting to find the class itself. BuiltinClassLoader (BuiltinClassLoader.java) is the base class for the three built-in loaders (bootstrap, platform, application). ClassLoaders (ClassLoaders.java) creates and provides access to these three built-in loaders via static fields BOOT_LOADER, PLATFORM_LOADER, and APP_LOADER. At the native level, classLoader.cpp implements the HotSpot C++ side of class loading, loading classes from the boot class path and modules image. SystemDictionary (systemDictionary.hpp) caches all loaded classes per ClassLoaderData and provides resolve_or_fail/resolve_or_null methods for class resolution with circularity detection.",
